name: Thomas Weaver
text: My wife and I joined Morningview after hearing the gospel being faithfully represented from the pulpit and lived out in the community of the congregation. The church has a commitment to theology and family ministry. The preaching is Christ centered and expository. The worship is a good mix of traditional and contemporary hymns with a focus on lyrics saturated in theological truths.

name: Franz Stagl
text: Faithful and expository preaching, a pastoral approach which is diminishing in today’s pulpit.  A very welcoming congregation which seeks unity and true fellowship.

name: Valarie French
text: I've never been to Morning View but I know David Day the missionary there. My family met him and his family a little over two years ago and were very impressed by the dedication they have to reaching the lost. He has a heart for people and I have seen him help many people in his different outreaches. He has inspired us to try to do more outreach and have more of a burden to tell of Jesus.

name: D Bebber
text: It is obvious that the pastor believes in God’s amazing grace in salvation. He holds dear to the truth that salvation is of God and for God’s glory. The pastor will make much of Christ every Sunday.

name: Darlene Hacker
text: Every Sunday my husband and I  are so very blessed to hear the goodness of God through CHurch Unlimited!!!! They are all about Jesus! Birmingham is way beyond blessed to have Pastor Brandon and Abbe ministering the love, total forgiveness, and the perfect completeness of the finished work of Christ's RIghteousness every Sunday!!! I have lived way too long under" get your behavior right then your life will change"....No No No...Know and understand the agape love of God through Jesus  and you will be radically changed...a heart transformation is what I am talking about!!!! I pray you will attend or tune in each Sunday to their "all about Jesus" sermons and you will will not be satisfied with anything less!!!
